<doc id="167588" wikidata="Q287021" url="?curid=167588" title="Mpg123">
<text>mpg123 is a free and open-source audio player. It supports MPEG audio formats, including MP3.

As a console application, it has no graphical user interface.

mpg123&#x27;s Assembly code is optimized with SIMD instructions to improve the performance of the iDCT part of the MPEG decoding.

mpg123&#x27;s decoding library, codice_1 is used by DeaDBeeF, Audacious, XMMS and Winamp (version 5.8) for MP3 playback and can be used in Winamp before version 5.8 via a plugin.

== History ==
The license for the last release (0.59r / 19 June 1999) from the original authors included restrictive (non-commercial, no-derivative) terms, although the source code was available. This led to the creation of mpg321, a similar program (based on MAD) licensed under the GPLv2. 

Official development of mpg123 and its library codice_2 stalled, and serious security holes emerged. Patches were applied downstream for packages provided by various Linux and BSD operating systems.

In 2006, a new maintainer started work towards the release of a new official mpg123 package. After several security rollup releases in the 0.6.x series, version 1.0 was released in 2007 under the LGPLv2.1, with codice_1 as a replacement for codice_2.

== See also ==

*Comparison of audio player software
*ogg123 (A similar program that plays Ogg Vorbis files. Released with the vorbis-tools reference software.)
*madplay

